  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Place your hand flat onto the <strong>chicken breast<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>and slice in half as if you were cutting a burger bun, but don't cut all the way through (think of the piece as an open book)</p>\r\n<p>Lay a sheet of cling film or greaseproof paper over the opened&nbsp;<strong>chicken breast</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s] </strong></span>and bash the&nbsp;<strong>chicken</strong> with a rolling pin to an even thickness throughout&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/811.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/811.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/811.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/811.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/811.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Crumble up the <strong>feta</strong></p>\r\n<p>Arrange the <strong>crumbled&nbsp;</strong><strong>feta </strong>over one side of the open&nbsp;<strong>chicken breast</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]</strong></span> and fold the other side over as though you're closing the book</p>\r\n<p>Secure&nbsp;the <strong>chicken breast</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]</strong></span> together by threading the <strong>skewer</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]</strong></span> through the opening (think sewing!)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/811.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/811.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/811.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/811.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/811.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a lid with a drizzle of&nbsp;<strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>chicken breast</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]</strong></span> and cook for 1-2 min on each side or until browned&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span>&nbsp;<strong>water</strong> to the&nbsp;pan</p>\r\n<p>Cover with a lid and cook for 12-16 min or until the chicken is cooked and the juices run clear</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, transfer to a chopping board to rest</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/811.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/811.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/811.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/811.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/811.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile,&nbsp;chop the <strong>potatoes </strong>(skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>potatoes</strong> to a pot with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cover the <strong>potatoes&nbsp;</strong>with <strong>boiled water</strong> and cook over a medium heat for 10-15 min or until tender&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, drain and leave&nbsp;to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/811.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/811.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/811.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/811.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/811.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>olives</strong> finely</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the<strong> garlic</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the<strong> chopped</strong>&nbsp;<strong>olives</strong>, <strong>chopped&nbsp;</strong><strong>garlic, dried oregano</strong>&nbsp;and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>olive oil</strong>&nbsp;to a <strong>pestle and mortar</strong></p>\r\n<p>Grind to a coarse paste - this is your <strong>tapenade</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/811.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/811.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/811.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/811.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/811.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Trim and finely slice the&nbsp;<strong>spring onion</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>Carefully slice the rested<strong> chicken</strong>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/811.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/811.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/811.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/811.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/811.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pot to a high heat with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive</strong> <strong>oil</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once the butter has melted, add the <strong>potatoes</strong>, <strong>spring onion</strong> and a generous pinch of both&nbsp;<strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\r\n<p>Lightly crush the potatoes with a masher and set them aside</p>\r\n<p>Wash, dry, then dress&nbsp;the <strong>rocket leaves</strong> with a splash of <strong>olive oil</strong></p>",
